    "The discussion in Section 6.1 further shows that this large-log R EXT Hα subsample also tends to have more regular variations of Hα activity.",
    "The long-term and regular variations of Hα activity suggest that the Hα variability of the subsample (with lower activity levels and large log R EXT Hα) might be associated with stellar activity cycles, i.e., long-term cyclic variations of Hα activity.",
